<title>MEXICO: Mexico's Zedillo says 53.6 bln pesos for telecomms.</title>
<headline>Mexico's Zedillo says 53.6 bln pesos for telecomms.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Private businesses in Mexico have pledged to invest 53.6 billion pesos in the telecommunications industry by the year 2000, President Ernesto Zedillo said on Friday.</p>
<p>&quot;Substantial private investments have been undertaken in telecommunications and new investments for more than 53.6 billion of today's pesos are planned from now until the year 2000,&quot; Zedillo said.</p>
<p>Zedillo spoke at a ceremony to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the foundation of Mexican construction firm Empresas ICA.</p>
<p>((--Debora Montesinos, Mexico City newsroom +525 728-7913))</p>
